    "what_description": "Oncoba cuneatoacuminata is a species of plant that belongs to the family Salicaceae. It is a woody climber or small tree that grows up to 15 meters in height, with a straight or slightly curved stem that has greyish-brown bark. The leaves are alternate, simple, and elliptical in shape, measuring 6-18 cm long and 2-7 cm wide, with a cuneate base and an acuminate tip, and are covered with a dense yellowish or brownish pubescence on both surfaces. The flowers are small, greenish-yellow, and arranged in axillary racemes, while the fruit is a drupe, measuring 1-2 cm long and 0.5-1 cm wide, with a single seed. The plant is found in tropical Africa, typically in secondary forests and along rivers.",
