    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Oncoba cuneatoacuminata are gastrointestinal issues, such as diarrhea and dysentery, which are caused by the plant's anthelmintic properties that kill parasitic worms. The plant's flavonoids and alkaloids have been shown to reduce inflammation and fight bacterial infections, making it effective in treating respiratory problems like bronchitis. Research has demonstrated that Oncoba cuneatoacuminata's antispasmodic properties help alleviate menstrual cramps and other symptoms associated with dysmenorrhea. Furthermore, the plant's antioxidant properties have been proven to protect against oxidative stress and cell damage, which can lead to cardiovascular diseases like high blood pressure. Additionally, the plant's antifungal properties make it effective in treating fungal infections like ringworm.",
