    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata are antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activities, which are attributed to its bioactive compounds such as flavonoids, saponins, and volatile oils. Antimicrobial activity is a significant property of this plant, exhibiting inhibitory effects against various pathogens, including bacteria and fungi, thereby preventing infections and promoting wound healing. The antioxidant property of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata helps to scavenge free radicals, thus protecting cells from oxidative damage and potentially mitigating conditions like cancer and neurodegenerative diseases. Additionally, this plant's anti-inflammatory property enables it to reduce inflammation and alleviate symptoms associated with conditions such as arthritis and other inflammatory disorders. Furthermore, the bioactive compounds present in Oncoba cuneatoacuminata also possess immunomodulatory activity, enhancing the immune system's response to infections and potentially aiding in the prevention and treatment of various diseases.",
