    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata are flavonoids, alkaloids, phenolic acids, and saponins. Flavonoids present in Oncoba cuneatoacuminata include quercetin, kaempferol, and isorhapontigenin which exhibit anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial properties. The alkaloids, including oncomine, oncoline, and oncoside, display anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and cytotoxic activities. Phenolic acids such as ferulic acid and caffeic acid contribute to the antioxidant and anti-inflammatory effects of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata. Saponins, a type of triterpenoid, are responsible for the plant's immunomodulatory and antiviral properties.",
