    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata are derived from its leaves and twigs, which are rich in flavonoids and alkaloids. Oncoba infusion is prepared by steeping the leaves in hot water, often used to treat fever and cough. Oncoba decoction is made by boiling the twigs and leaves in water, traditionally used to manage diarrhea and dysentery. Oncoba tincture is a concentrated liquid extract prepared using ethanol or glycerin, commonly used as a digestive aid and to treat respiratory issues. Oncoba tea and ointment preparations involve drying and processing the leaves and twigs into a form suitable for topical application, often used to treat skin irritations and wounds.",
