    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Oncoba cuneatoacuminata improperly include diarrhea and vomiting due to its emetic and purgative properties, leading to nausea in some individuals. These gastrointestinal issues can be caused by the plant's active compounds, particularly glycosides, which can irritate the stomach and intestines. In rare cases, the misuse of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata may also induce seizures, especially in individuals with a history of epilepsy or those taking certain medications that interact with the plant's compounds. This is because the plant contains alkaloids that can affect the nervous system and alter brain activity. Overall, the improper use of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata can lead to a range of adverse effects, highlighting the need for careful handling and dosing under the guidance of a qualified healthcare professional.",
    "uses": "Oncoba cuneatoacuminata has been found to have various medicinal properties, including antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory effects. Its extracts have been used to treat conditions such as fever, rheumatism, and skin infections. The plant's leaves and roots are traditionally used in folk medicine to treat various ailments, including respiratory and gastrointestinal issues. In some parts of Africa, Oncoba cuneatoacuminata is used to treat snakebites and other venomous bites. Further research is needed to fully understand the plant's potential medicinal applications and benefits.",
    "taxonomy": "Oncoba cuneatoacuminata is classified under the family Ochnaceae. It is a species of flowering plant. Oncoba cuneatoacuminata is native to tropical Africa. The plant is further classified under the genus Oncoba. It is a small shrub or tree with medicinal properties.",
    "benefits": "Oncoba cuneatoacuminata has been traditionally used in various cultures for its medicinal properties, and research suggests that it has potential health benefits. The plant has been found to exhibit anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant properties. These properties may contribute to the treatment of various health conditions, including infections and inflammatory diseases. Additionally, the plant has been used to treat fever, diarrhea, and respiratory issues. Further studies are needed to fully understand the health benefits of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata and its potential applications in traditional medicine.",
    "parts": "Oncoba cuneatoacuminata is a plant species that has been studied for its potential medicinal properties. The roots of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata are reported to have antimicrobial and antidiabetic properties. The leaves of the plant are also used in traditional medicine, particularly for their antiseptic and anti-inflammatory effects. The bark and roots of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata are used to treat various health issues, including fever and digestive problems. Further research is needed to fully understand the medicinal properties and potential uses of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata.",
    "intro": "Oncoba cuneatoacuminata, also known as the African dogwood or wild dogwood, is a species of flowering plant in the family Salicaceae. This plant has been found to possess several health benefits, including anti-inflammatory, antibacterial, and antifungal properties, which can aid in the treatment of various ailments such as fever, skin infections, and digestive issues. The bioactive constituents of Oncoba cuneatoacuminata include flavonoids, alkaloids, and saponins, which contribute to its medicinal properties. In traditional African medicine, the plant is often used to prepare herbal remedies, including infusions, decoctions, and tinctures, which are commonly used to treat fever, cough, and respiratory issues."
